# 58_actions_container_smoke — Tier 2 m8 Container ops sweep (s255).
# Validates the six wrap-now Container-ops verbs migrated from raw
# `add_action` to `add_scripted_action`:
#   - Clip:  clip-make / clip-release
#   - Blend: blend-make / blend-release
#   - Warp:  warp-make / warp-release
#
# Sibling smoke to 52-57, same conservative-shape posture. All six
# are member-stored with sensitivity pumps (clip uses defensive
# canvas-side guards rather than a pump; blend has the exactly-2
# pump per s122-style; warp uses update_warp_action_sensitive). The
# disabled-action-fires-anyway shape applies (documented in m5).
#
# **Per audit note (line 148-152):** group-make / group-release are
# bucket B (covered by `objects.group` / `objects.ungroup`) and are
# NOT in this sweep. The six verbs above are the audit's full
# "Container ops not in objects" set.
#
# **warp-edit / warp-flatten are bucket C** per fork #7 (slated for
# deprecation when the inspector subsumes them) and stay raw.
#
# ── What this smoke exercises ─────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Nine observables: 1 list + 6 invocations + 2 refusals.
#
# ── Caller / mask ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# ScripterWindow listener, RunContext::Scripter. All six verbs declare
# Scripter | TestRunner. Macro is OUT.
#
# ── Test isolation ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Mutations applied to whatever's selected, in order:
#
#   - `win clip-make`     — if 2+ selected, top object becomes clip
#                           mask over the rest.
#   - `win clip-release`  — if a clip group selected, releases it.
#                           After phase 2, this likely reverses it.
#   - `win blend-make`    — if exactly 2 selected, makes blend node.
#                           Otherwise no-op at canvas layer.
#   - `win blend-release` — if a blend selected, releases it.
#   - `win warp-make`     — if eligible selection, creates a warp.
#                           on_warp_make may open a popover/dialog;
#                           the trace channel still says `ok`.
#   - `win warp-release`  — releases warp if one selected.
#
# Visual channel needs varied state to be fully legible. Safe to run
# on any state — all six canvas-side handlers defend against bad input.
#
# ── Precondition reminders ────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# 1. Curvz running with project + doc open.
# 2. For visual: select 2+ objects (clip / blend) or an existing
#    container (release verbs). Trace channel passes regardless.

#[sub] === Phase 1: registry sanity-check — `win` is still registered ===

list

#[sub] === Phase 2: clip-make verb is addressable ===

win clip-make

#[sub] === Phase 3: clip-release verb is addressable ===

win clip-release

#[sub] === Phase 4: blend-make verb is addressable ===

win blend-make

#[sub] === Phase 5: blend-release verb is addressable ===

win blend-release

#[sub] === Phase 6: warp-make verb is addressable ===

#[sub] Note: on_warp_make may open a dialog/popover depending on
#[sub] selection state. Trace channel passes regardless; visual
#[sub] channel may show a UI element pop up.

win warp-make

#[sub] === Phase 7: warp-release verb is addressable ===

win warp-release

#[sub] === Phase 8: unknown-verb refusal ===

win quit

#[sub] === Phase 9: extra-argument refusal ===

win clip-make "argument"

